\begin_layout Section
Proof derivations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We give a more flexible set of macros that allows the construction of proof
 derivations.
 Example:
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\bussproof{\unaryinf{\binaryinf{\axiom{\Gamma}{A\vee B,\Delta}}{\binaryinf{\unaryinf{\axiomc{}}AA{(ax)}}{\unaryinf{\axiomc{}}BB{(ax)}}{A\vee B}{A,B}{(\ensuremath{\vee\vdash})}}{\Gamma}{A,B,\Delta}{(cut)}}{\Gamma}{A\vee B,\Delta}{(\ensuremath{\vdash\vee})}}\end{align*}

\end_inset

All proof derivations begin with a 
\family typewriter

\backslash
bussproof
\family default
 macro in a math environment.
 Then the tree of the derivation is specified from bottom to top using the
 macros 
\family typewriter

\backslash
unaryinf
\family default
, 
\family typewriter

\backslash
binaryinf
\family default
, etc., described below, starting with the root inference.
 Then the leaves of the tree must be put inside an 
\family typewriter

\backslash
axiom
\family default
 or an 
\family typewriter

\backslash
axiomc
\family default
 macro.
\end_layout

